7 MW Championship Game|url=http://www.ktvb.com/sports/ncaaf/boise-state/boise-state-and-san-diego-state-picked-to-meet-in-2017-mw-championship-game/459373224|website=KTVB.com|publisher=TEGNA|date=July 25, 2017|accessdate=July 27, 2017}}</ref> Sr. OL Mason Hampton was selected to the all-conference first team offense. Jr. DL David Moa and Jr. DB Tyler Horton were selected to the all-conference first team defense.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gagliardi|first1=Robert|title=UW's Allen, Wingard named preseason MW players of the year|url=http://www.wyosports.net/university_of_wyoming/football/uw-s-allen-wingard-named-preseason-mw-players-of-the/article_70219352-7142-11e7-ba68-2fb8eec27695.html|website=WyoSports.net|date=July 25, 2017|accessdate=July 27, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Media poll===\n====Mountain Division====\n# Boise State \u2013 161 (21)\n# Colorado State \u2013 135 (6)\n# Wyoming \u2013 114 (1)\n# Air Force \u2013 82\n# New Mexico \u2013 68\n# Utah State \u2013 28\n\n==Schedule==\n{{CFB schedule\n| rankyear = 2017\n| poll = [[2017 NCAA Division I FBS football rankings#AP Poll|AP Poll]] released prior to game\n| timezone = Mountain\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 2\n| time = 1:45 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| rank = \n| opponent = [[2017 Troy Trojans football team|Troy]]\n| site_stadium = [[Albertsons Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Boise, Idaho|Boise, ID]]\n| tv = [[ESPNU College Football|ESPNU]]\n| score = 24\u201313\n| attend = 31,581\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 9\n| time = 8:30 p.m.\n| w/l = l\n| nonconf = y\n| away = y\n| rank = \n| opponent = [[2017 Washington State Cougars football team|Washington State]]\n| opprank = 20\n| site_stadium = [[Martin Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Pullman, Washington|Pullman, WA]]\n| tv = [[ESPN College Football Saturday Primetime|ESPN]]\n| score = 44\u201347\n| overtime = 3OT\n| attend = 32,631\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = {{Tooltip|September 14|Thursday}}\n| time = 6:00 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| rank = \