P Ananda]]''''' - [[Bengali-language]] news channel in India. Formerly known as Star Ananda.\n*'''''[[ABP Ganga]]''''' - Hindi-language news channel for [[Uttar Pradesh]] & [[Uttarakhand]] states in India.\n*'''''[[ABP Sanjha]]''''' - [[Punjabi language|Punjabi-language]] news channel in India.<ref>{{cite web|title=ABP Sanjha Official|url=http://abpsanjha.abplive.in/}}</ref>\n*'''''[[ABP Majha]]''''' - [[Marathi-language]] news channel in India. Formerly known as Star Majha.\n*'''''[[ABP Asmita]]''''' - [[Gujarati language|Gujarati-language]] news channel in India.\n*'''''ABP Live''''' - English-language digital news channel.\n*'''''[[ABP Andhra]]''''' - [[Telugu-language]] news channel in India.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.televisionpost.com/abp-news-network-receives-four-tv-channel-licences-from-mib/|title=ABP News Network receives four TV channel licences from MIB - TelevisionPost: Latest News, India\u2019s Television, Cable, DTH, TRAI|date=2019-03-08|website=TelevisionPost: Latest News, India\u2019s Television, Cable, DTH,  TRAI|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-08}}</ref>\n*'''''[[ABP Tamil]]''''' - [[Tamil-language]] news channel in India.<sup></sup><ref name=\":0\" />\n*'''''[[ABP Kannada]]''''' - [[Kannada-language]] news channel in India.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Awards==\n* The House of Ananda awards the ''[[Ananda Purashkar]]'' every year to writers writing in [[Bengali language|Bengali]].{{citation needed|date=April 2012}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.abp.in/ ABP Corporate Website]\n* [http://www.abpweddings.com/ ABP Group weddings page]\n{{ABP Group}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:ABP Group}}\n[[Category:ABP Group]]\n[[Category:Book publishing companies of India]]\n[[Category:Newspaper companies of India]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Kolkata]]\n[[Category:Media companies established in 1922]]\n\n\n{{media-company-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Revirvlkodlaku", "label": "safe", "comment": "Cleaned up usingAutoEd| Alt