esplat]]\n|-\n| rowspan=11| [[Saturn Awards]]<ref name=\"saturnawards\">{{cite web |url=http://www.saturnawards.org/ |title=RISE OF THE PLANET OF THE APES and SUPER 8 lead Saturn Awards with 3 awards each. |date=26 July 2012 |work=saturnawards.org |accessdate=27 July 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120626144753/http://www.saturnawards.org/ |archivedate=26 June 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Fantasy Film|Best Fantasy Film]]\n| {{Won}}\n| Steven Godfrey, Pietro Ponti, Tania Marie Richard, Andy Warren\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Director|Best Director]]\n| {{nom}}\n| [[David Yates]]\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Saturn Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]]\n| {{nom}}\n| [[Ralph Fiennes]]\n|-\n| {{nom}}\n| [[Alan Rickman]]\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]]\n| {{nom}}\n| [[Emma Watson]]\n|-\n| Best Production Design\n| {{nom}}\n| [[Stuart Craig]]\n|-\n| Best Editing\n| {{nom}}\n| Mark Day\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Costume|Best Costume]]\n| {{nom}}\n| Jany Temime\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Make-up|Best Make-up]]\n| {{nom}}\n| Nick Dudman, Amanda Knight\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Special Effects|Best Special Effects]]\n| {{nom}}\n| Tim Burke, Greg Butler, John Richardson, David Vickery\n|-\n| [[Hugo Award]]s<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thehugoawards.org/hugo-history/2012-hugo-awards/ |title=2012 Hugo Awards |publisher=[[Hugo Award]]s |accessdate=10 April 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/66nnsGGRI?url=http://www.thehugoawards.org/hugo-history/2012-hugo-awards/ |archivedate=9 April 2012}}</ref>\n| [[Hugo Award for Best Dramatic Presentation, Long Form|Best Dramatic Presentation, Long Form]]\n| {{nom}}\n| [[David Yates]], [[Steve Kloves]]\n|-\n| rowspan=7| [[2012 MTV Movie Awards|MTV Movie Awards]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2012/06/03/mtv-movie-awards-winners/ |title=MTV Movie Awards: Check out the winners here |work=Entertainment Weekly |date=3 June 2012 |accessdate=3 June 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Warner |first=Kara |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1684181/2012-mtv-movie-awards-nominees.jhtml |title=2012 MTV Movie Awards Nominees: The Full List |publisher=[[MTV News]] |date=30 April 2012 |accessdate=3 November 2012}}</ref>\n| [[MTV Movie Award for Best Movie|Movie of the Year]]\n| {{nom}}\n| ''Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows&nbsp;\u2013 Part 2''\n|-\n| [[MTV Movie Award for Best Performance|Best Male Performance]]\n| {{nom}}\n| Daniel Radcliffe\n|-\n| [[MTV Movie Award for Best Performance|Best Female Performance]]\n| {{nom}}\n| Emma Watson\n|-\n| [[MTV Movie Award for Best Hero|Best Hero]]\n| {{won}}\n| Daniel Radcliffe\n|-\n| [[MTV Movie Award for Best Kiss|Best Kiss]]\n| {{nom}}\n| Rupert Grint and Emma Watson\n|-\n| [[MTV Movie Award for Best Fight|Best Fight]]\n| {{nom}}\n| Daniel Radcliffe and Ralph Fiennes\n|-\n| [[MTV Movie Award for Best On-Screen Duo|Best Cast]]\n| {{won}}\n| Daniel Radcliffe, Rupert Grint, Emma Watson, Tom Felton\n|-\n| rowspan=5|[[17th Empire Awards]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Empire Awards 2012 |url=http://www.empireonline.com/awards2012/winners/film.asp |work=[[Sky Movies]] |publisher=[[Empire (film magazine)|Empire]] |accessdate=9 December 2012}}</ref>\n| Best Film\n| {{Won}}\n| ''Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows&nbsp;\u2013 Part 2''\n|-\n| Best Actor\n| {{nom}}\n| [[Daniel Radcliffe]]\n|-\n| Best Director\n| {{Won}}\n| [[David Yates]]\n|-\n| Best 3D\n| {{nom}}\n| ''Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows&nbsp;\u2013 Part 2''\n|-\n| Best Female Newcomer\n| {{nom}}\n| [[Bonnie Wright]]\n|}\n<!-- PLACE EXTRA AWARDS ABOVE -->\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows (film)}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.harrypotterwizardscollection.com/}}\n* {{IMDb title|1201607}}\n* {{Amg movie|434402}}\n* {{Rotten-tomatoes|harry_potter_and_the_deathly_hallows_part_2_2011}}\