{"title_page": "The Italian Flag", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name         = The Italian Flag\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Prolapse (band)]]\n| cover        = [[File:Prolapse,_Front_Cover,_The_Italian_Flag.jpg|250px]]\n| alt          = \n| released     = October 1997\n| recorded     = \n| venue        = \n| studio       =\n| genre        = *[[post punk]]\n*[[indie rock]]\n| length       = 69:07\n| label        = [[Radar Records]]\n| producer     = [[Donald Ross Skinner]]\n| prev_title   = [[backsaturday]]\n| prev_year    = 1995\n| next_title   = [[Ghost of Dead Aeroplanes]]\n| next_year    = 1999\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = The Italian Flag\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Killing The Bland\n | single1date = 1997\n | single2     = Autocade\n | single2date = 1997\n | single3     = Deanshanger\n | single3date = 1998\n }}\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n|rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n|rev1score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/the-italian-flag-mw0000045496 |title=The Italian Flag \u2013 Prolapse &#124; AllMusic |work=allmusic.com}}</ref>\n}}\n__NOTOC__\n'''''The Italian Flag''''', is the third album by the band [[Prolapse (band)|Prolapse]], released in October 1997 on [[Radar Records]] in the UK. The album was produced by [[Donald Ross Skinner]], who then joined the band, playing on the subsequent tours to support the album's release.\n\nThe album was originally released on double 12\u201d vinyl and CD by [[Radar Records]] in the UK & Europe, and on CD by [[Jetset Records]] in the US.\n\n==Track listing==\nAll songs written by Prolapse\n\n{{Tracklist\n| headline        = Side 1\n| title1          = Slash/Oblique\n| length1         = 4:55\n| title2          = Deanshanger\n| length2         = 4:18\n| title3          = Cacophony No.A\n| length3         = 5:06\n| title4          = Killing The Bland\n| length4         = 2:27\n| total_length    = 16:46\n}}\n{{Tracklist\n| headline        = Side 2\n| title1          = I Hate The Clicking Man\n| length1         = 5:15\n| title2          = Autocade\n| length2         = 4:40\n| title3          = Tunguska\n| length3         = 4:01\n| title4          = Flat Velocity Curve\n| length4         = 7:16\n| total_length    = 21:12\n}}\n{{Tracklist\n| headline        = Side 3\n| title1          = Return Of Shoes\n| length1         = 5:42\n| title2          = A Day At Death Seaside\n| length2         = 3:31\n| title3          = Bruxelles\n| length3         = 5:56\n| title4          = Visa For Violet And Van\n| length4         = 5:55\n| total_length    = 21.04\n}}\n{{Tracklist\n| headline        = Side 4\n| title1          = Three Wooden Heads\n| length1         = 10:05\n| total_length    = 10:05\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n===Band===\n* Mick Derrick - vocals, stylophone\n* Mick Harrison - bass, guitar\n* David Jeffreys - guitar, vocals\n* Pat Marsden - guitar, keyboards\n* Tim Pattinson - drums\n* Linda Steelyard - vocals, keyboard, recorder\n===Production===\n* Produced by [[Donald Ross Skinner]]\n* Recorded & Mixed by Martin Wilding (except ''Killing The Bland'' and ''Visa For Violet And Van'')\n* Recorded by Paul Kendall (''Killing The Bland'' and ''Visa For Violet And Van'' recording only)\n* Artwork by Matthew Cooper, Mick Harrison, Paul Harrison\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Prolapse (band)}}\n\n[[Category:1997 albums]]\n[[Category:Radar Records albums]]\n[[Category:Prolapse albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name         = The Italian Flag\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Prolapse (band)]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = October 1997\n| recorded     = \n| venue        = \n| studio       =\n| genre        = *[[post punk]]\n*[[indie rock]]\n| length       = 69:07\n| label        = [[Radar Records]]\n| producer     = [[Donald Ross Skinner]]\n| prev_title   = [[backsaturday]]\n| prev_year    = 1995\n| next_title   = [[Ghost of Dead Aeroplanes]]\n| next_year    = 1999\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = The Italian Flag\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Killing The Bland\n | single1date = 1997\n | single2     = Autocade\n | single2date = 1997\n | single3     = Deanshanger\n | single3date = 1998\n }}\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n|rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n|rev1score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/the-italian-flag-mw0000045496 |title=The Italian Flag \u2013 Prolapse &#124; AllMusic |work=allmusic.com}}</ref>\n}}\n__NOTOC__\n'''''The Italian Flag''''', is the third album by the band [[Prolapse (band)|Prolapse]], released in October 1997 on [[Radar Records]] in the UK. The album was produced by [[Donald Ross Skinner]], who then joined the band, playing on the subsequent tours to support the album's release.\n\nThe album was originally released on double 12\u201d vinyl and CD by [[Radar Records]] in the UK & Europe, and on CD by [[Jetset Records]] in the US.\n\n==Track listing==\nAll songs written by Prolapse\n\n{{Tracklist\n| headline        = Side 1\n| title1          = Slash/Oblique\n| length1         = 4:55\n| title2          = Deanshanger\n| length2         = 4:18\n| title3          = Cacophony No.A\n| length3         = 5:06\n| title4          = Killing The Bland\n| length4         = 2:27\n| total_length    = 16:46\n}}\n{{Tracklist\n| headline        = Side 2\n| title1          = I Hate The Clicking Man\n| length1         = 5:15\n| title2          = Autocade\n| length2         = 4:40\n| title3          = Tunguska\n| length3         = 4:01\n| title4          = Flat Velocity Curve\n| length4         = 7:16\n| total_length    = 21:12\n}}\n{{Tracklist\n| headline        = Side 3\n| title1          = Return Of Shoes\n| length1         = 5:42\n| title2          = A Day At Death Seaside\n| length2         = 3:31\n| title3          = Bruxelles\n| length3         = 5:56\n| title4          = Visa For Violet And Van\n| length4         = 5:55\n| total_length    = 21.04\n}}\n{{Tracklist\n| headline        = Side 4\n| title1  